result.execSummary:
The defendant James Lee Henriksen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:41 AM - case called.  Defendant James Lee Henriksen in court.  Attorney Wright C. Laufenberg in court for James Lee Henriksen.  Attorney Andrew R Polzin in court for State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Polzin regarding plea agreement.  Court questions Atty Laufenberg/Defendant.  Responses by Atty Laufenberg/Defendant.  State moves to amend Count 1 to misdemeanor bail jumping.  Court grants motion to amend Count 1.  Plea to an amended Count 1 is no contest.  Waiver of rights and tendering plea.  Waiver free and voluntary.  Factual basis exits for plea.  Found guilty by the Court on Count 1.  Count 2 - DRI.  Joint recommendation.  Statement by Atty Polzin/Atty Laufenberg/Court regarding sentencing.  Court orders a fine in the amount of $75.00 plus cc/sc to be paid in 60 days unless payment arraignments are made with the Court.  Post conviction rights given.
